ry:John Jay| ]]\n[[Category:1745 births]]\n[[Category:1829 deaths]]\n[[Category:18th-century American diplomats]]\n[[Category:18th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:18th-century American judges]]\n[[Category:American abolitionists]]\n[[Category:American Bible Society]]\n[[Category:American people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:American people of French descent]]\n[[Category:American slave owners]]\n[[Category:Chief Justices of the United States]]\n[[Category:Columbia College (New York) alumni]]\n[[Category:Continental Congressmen from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Federalist Party state governors of the United States]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]\n[[Category:Governors of New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Huguenot participants in the American Revolution]]\n[[Category:Members of the American Antiquarian Society]]\n[[Category:New York (state) Federalists]]\n[[Category:New York (state) lawyers]]\n[[Category:People of colonial New York]]\n[[Category:People from Bedford, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Katonah, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Rye, New York]]\n[[Category:The Federalist Papers]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1789 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 1796 United States presidential election]]\n[[Category:United States Secretaries of State]]\n[[Category:1800 United States vice-presidential candidates]]\n[[Category:Washington administration cabinet members]]\n[[Category:United States federal judges admitted to the practice of law by reading law]]\n[[Category:Van Cortlandt family]]\n[[Category:Members of the New York Manumission Society]]\n[[Category:United States Secretary of Foreign Affairs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American politician, diplomat, and Founding Father}}\n{{other uses|John Jay (disambiguation)}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name          = John Jay\n| image         = John Jay (Gilbert Stuart portrait).jpg \n| captio