os Aires Province|Buenos Aires]]) is an Argentine retired [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] and football coach.\n\n==Club career==\nGalv\u00e1n started his career at [[Racing Club de Avellaneda]] in 1992, before moving to [[Brazil]] in 1998 to play for [[Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro]].\n\nIn Brazil he was seen as a skilled defender. His technique was at its best when playing as a sweeper. He scored some key goals. He has a powerful header and sense for positioning.\n\nAmong other titles, he won the [[Campeonato Mineiro|Minas Gerais state]] with Atl\u00e9tico Minero. He was also in the Atl\u00e9tico Minero side that were runners-up in the [[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|Brazilian Championship]] in 1999 and with [[Santos F.C.|Santos]] in 2000 when they won the [[Campeonato Paulista|S\u00e3o Paulo State Championship]]. He played for two years at each team in Brazil. In 1998, with Atl\u00e9tico, he has involved in a fight at [[Esporte Clube Vit\u00f3ria|Vit\u00f3ria]]'s stadium, where he was one of four players from each side sent off. He also scored an own goal at [[Est\u00e1dio Vila Belmiro|Vila Belmiro]], in a 2-0 defeat against Santos' biggest rivals, [[Sport Club Corinthians Paulista|Corinthians]]. He also played for [[Paysandu Sport Club|Paysandu]], in 2004.\n\nGalv\u00e1n returned to Argentina in 2002 to play for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Lan\u00fas]] and in 2004 he had a brief spell with [[Ciudad de Murcia]] in [[Spain]]. He has also played for [[Olimpia Asunci\u00f3n|Club Olimpia]] in [[Paraguay]] and [[Argentinos Juniors]] in Argentina.\n\nIn 2007 Galv\u00e1n joined Peruvian team [[Universitario de Deportes]], in February 2009 he announced that he plans to retire in December 2010 to take up a position as a youth coach with the club.<ref>[http://www.rpp.com.pe/2009-02-28-carlos-galvan-anuncia-que-se-retirara-el-2010-en-universitario-noticia_167231.html Carlos Galv\u00e1n anuncia que se retirar\u00e1 el 2010 en Universitario] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090303232338/http://www.rpp.com.pe/2009-02-28-carlos-galvan-anuncia-que-se-retirara-el-2010-en-universitario-noticia_167231.html |date=March 3, 2009 }} at rpp.com {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n'''[[Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro]]'''\n*'''[[Campeonato Mineiro]] (2):''' [[Campeonato Mineiro|1999]], [[Campeonato Mineiro|2000]]\n\n'''[[Santos FC]]'''\n*'''[[Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A]] (1):''' [[2002 Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A|2002]]\n\n'''[[Universitario de Deportes]]'''\n*'''[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n Peruana|Torneo Apertura 2008]] (1):''' [[2008 Torneo Descentralizado|2008]]\n*'''[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n Peruana]] (1):''' [[2009 Torneo Descentralizado|2009]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{ESPN FC|72752}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120217215531/http://www.futbolxxi.com/Futbolista.aspx?ID=4547&SEOFutbolista=Galvan+Carlos+Alberto+(Negro) Argentine Primera statistics]{{in lang|es}}\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|57228-carlos-galvan}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Galvan, Carlos}}\n[[Category:1973 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Buenos Aires Province]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Racing Club de Avellaneda footballers]]\n[[Category:Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro players]]\n[[Category:Santos FC players]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico Lan\u00fas footballers]]\n[[Category:Ciudad de Murcia footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentinos Juniors footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Olimpia footballers]]\n[[Category:Banfield footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Universitario de Deportes footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Deportivo Universidad C\u00e9sar Vallejo footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Peruvian Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Paraguay]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Peru]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n", "name_user": "Zyxw", "label": "safe", "comment": "update FootballDatabase.eu template, misc formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Galv%C3%A1n"}
